Scroll down and click Commit new file
Done. It'll be at the root, not in src.

Every time I try to do this and always ends up and that stupid SRC file

The issue is you're already inside the src folder when you hit "Add file" - GitHub defaults to creating there.

Here's the fix:

Go to your main repo page (ApexTrade-backend) - click the repo name at the top
Make sure you're at the root (you'll see the folders like src, not files inside src)
Then click Add file
Name it .env.example
Add the content and commit
That's it. The key is being at the root before you add the file.


Ask me anything...
